==Finnish==
===Noun===
romani
# (''person'') One of the [[roma]] communtiy or descent, a [[Rom]] or [[gypsy]]
# (''language'') [[romany]]

===Usage notes===

This is the official term to be used in official talk. However, as it is usually pronunced with two "a"'s, it is homophonic to [[romaani]], a [[novel]] (book of fiction). Therefore it leaves room for the old pun about the library bus. ''Meidänkin kylään saatiin kirjastoauto: Kuusi romaania Volkswagen Minibussissa!'' Now our village has the library bus too: Six Rom in a Volkswagen Mini Bus.

===Synonyms===
*[[mustalainen]] (1)
*[[romanikieli]], [[mustalaiskieli]] (2)
